  "commit_message": "Fix a crash in `consider-using-enumerate` for non-name loop targets (#11067)\n\nfix(refactoring): prevent consider-using-enumerate crash on non-name loop target\n\n`_check_consider_using_enumerate` accessed `node.target.name` unconditionally, which raised `AttributeError` when the loop target was not a plain variable (e.g. `for self.idx in range(len(x))`), where `node.target` is an `AssignAttr`/`Tuple`/`Subscript` with no `.name`.\n\nGuard with an `AssignName` check and return early. This is also the ",
